  "text": "The phase factor from (87) does not affect the eigenvalues of the correlation matrix, which we can see as follows. The eigenvalue equation for the correlation matrix is given by j C ij φ k (j) = ζ k φ k (i). Hence, the phase factor in C ij can be absorbed into the φ k (i), φ k (j)'s so that ζ k remain the same. Modulo the phase factor, the correlation matrix from this problem is identical to what is found for a 1D tight-binding electron, but with a Fermi wavevector of k 0 /2 [CITATION_1] . The entanglement entropy is given by",
